  "prompt": "What is the difference between chocolate and truffles?",
  "response": "Chocolate is a sweet food made from cacao beans, typically in the form of a solid bar or liquid. It comes in various forms such as milk, dark, and white chocolate, and can be consumed on its own or used as an ingredient in desserts, confections, and baked goods.\n\nTruffles, on the other hand, are a type of chocolate confectionery. They are usually made from a ganache center\u2014a mixture of chocolate and cream\u2014which is then coated with cocoa powder, nuts, or more chocolate. Truffles are often round and bite-sized, and they are named after the rare and expensive fungus they resemble.\n\nIn summary, all truffles are chocolate-based confections, but not all chocolate is truffles. Chocolate is a broader category that encompasses various forms and uses, while truffles are a specific type of chocolate confection.",
